k(A) = k *[ \space T(x_1) \space T(x_2) \space ... \space T(x_n) \space ] = [\space kT(x_1) \space kT(x_2) \space ... \space kT(x_n) \space ] = [ \space (kT)(x_1) \space (kT)(x_2) \space ... \space (kT)(x_n) \space]
1 \times (0+0)=1
1 \times 0+1 \times 0=0
 \begin{array}{c|cc} + & 0 & 1 \\ \hline 0 & 0 & 1 \\ 1 & 1 & 0 \\ \end{array} \qquad \begin{array}{c|cc} \times & 0 & 1 \\ \hline 0 & 0 & 0 \\ 1 & 1 & 1 \\ \end{array} 
 \begin{array}{c|cc} + & 0 & 1 & 2 & 3 \\ \hline 0 & 0 & 1 & 2 & 3 \\ 1 & 1 & 0 & 3 & 2 \\ 2 & 2 & 3 & 0 & 1 \\ 3 & 3 & 2 & 1 & 0 \\ \end{array} \qquad \begin{array}{c|cc} \times & 0 & 1 & 2 & 3 \\ \hline 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 & 0 \\ 1 & 0 & 1 & 2 & 3 \\ 2 & 2 & 2 & 2 & 2 \\ 3 & 0 & 3 & 2 & 3 \\ \end{array} 
2 \times (0+0)=2
2 \times 0 + 0 \times 2=0
